results.title: The Fountain of Goof F.O.G. Tv Network The Man from Godsvilla
results.description:
The Fountain of Goof (F.O.G.) Tv Network) 

Movie:  The Man from Godsvilla

Season 1

Episode 1:  A storm brews out in the open sea near a tropical area called Germuda - it's forceful winds swirls about...growing quickly into a tropical storm...then...into a full force hurricane.  And...as it travels along the same old path of destruction like similar storms...this particular one unexpectedly and unseasonly spreads quickly. 

Episode 2:  News media "whether-men" warns all citizens who live along hurricane alley...once again predict its exact date, time and location it will hit landfall.

Episode 3:  This now upgraded category 6 hurricane named King-Pong begins to work it's way thru...with wind gusts extremely high...not even the most experienced whether-men had predicted...showing multiple radar satellite images...issues mass warnings as they shift everyone into "Panic Mode."

Episode 4:  The storm's angry wrath germinates almost a sickening, contagious disease of growing anger and fear as though this seemingly powerful hurricane was attempting to spread along its usual route...to reach and destroy solid structures, plant life and hurt anyone without care.

Episode 5:  An old man who lived in a town called Godsvilla his entire life didn't panic...or worry...or felt fearful...but...sat quiet and calmly in his fishing lounge chair outside..near the front door of his house...holding a cigar in one hand and a can of beer in the other. 

Episode 6:  The man from Godsvilla waited and watched hurricane King-Pong flood waters rise in his driveway, from 2ft. to 3ft. and at nearly 4ft..  He calmly puts his fishing cap on...lights up his cigar and pops open the beer can...and bravely waits to see what is going to come about...

Reader:  Please keep in mind...this scene is not at all similar to an old movie classic about a large ocean passenger liner that hits an iceberg...where a wealthy dressed gentleman and his assistant freely gave up their life vests to another...prepared "to go down with the ship like gentlemen" while sipping a glass of brandy...but the opposite...the man from Godsvilla faced his fears...holds a cigar, prepares to celebrate and to toast another battle even tho all of his physical belongings are no longer...knowing well that they can easily be replaced.  It was his remarkable courage, calmness and confidence he maintained whatever came his way...a "bring it on" kind of survival mode"...letting things just unfold all on its own...not letting anyone direct or control him to give up...

(tho it was probably a dangerous decision to stay...he made his own choice).

to be continued...

Esther Monsalve
The Angel Shop

p.s.  there is calm after the storm as well...

Support Operation Smile

Note: Please use MEMO, an editor writing software, in oder to open this digital file.
